<p>Subject does not meet <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NHOCKEY" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NHOCKEY">WP:NHOCKEY</a>. Of the leagues he's played in, only the AHL and DEL count towards #2 and he played a total of 129 games where at least 200 is needed to pass. If the I-divisioona was to count like its current form Mestis does he would have 153 games which still leaves him short of 200. He also has no preeminent honours of note and never played for Canada in the IIHF World Championship. <a href="/wiki/User:Tay87" title="User:Tay87">Tay87</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Tay87" title="User talk:Tay87">talk</a>) 23:35, 12 August 2019 (UTC)
</p>

<ul><li><b>Keep</b> If the Victoria and Albert Museum and the Museum of Modern Art in NY think he is notable by placing him in their collections, he probably is. He also meets our WP:ARTIST 4d standard for several museums. Vexations and I have added many sources; there are now 14.<a href="/wiki/User:ThatMontrealIP" title="User:ThatMontrealIP">ThatMontrealIP</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:ThatMontrealIP" title="User talk:ThatMontrealIP">talk</a>) 03:27, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Keep</b> Plenty of references, death noted in The New York Times, art pieces in the collection of major museums, the subject of a major retrospective accompanied by a 70-page booklet about his art. This is a no-brainer. <a href="/wiki/User:Pichpich" title="User:Pichpich">Pichpich</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Pichpich" title="User talk:Pichpich">talk</a>) 03:38, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Keep</b> - in fairness to the editor who sent this to AfD <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Robert_Farber_(artist)&amp;oldid=910561232">this</a> was the state of the article when it was submitted. Under those circumstances, it probably could have even been speedied as not making a claim of notability. As it stands now, notability is not in question. <a href="/wiki/User:EnPassant" title="User:EnPassant">♟♙</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:EnPassant" title="User talk:EnPassant">talk</a>) 18:41, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Keep</b> Meets <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:ARTIST" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:ARTIST">WP:ARTIST</a> by having work in MoMA and V&amp;A's collections. -<a href="/wiki/User:Lopifalko" title="User:Lopifalko">Lopifalko</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Lopifalko" title="User talk:Lopifalko">talk</a>) 19:03, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Andrew_Pawiak"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Pawiak&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Andrew Pawiak (page does not exist)">Andrew Pawiak</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Andrew_Pawiak&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<dl><dd><span id="Andrew_Pawiak"></span><span class="plainlinks nourlexpansion lx"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Pawiak&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Andrew Pawiak (page does not exist)">Andrew Pawiak</a> (<a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Pawiak&amp;action=edit">edit</a>&#160;&#124; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Talk:Andrew_Pawiak&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Talk:Andrew Pawiak (page does not exist)">talk</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Pawiak&amp;action=history">history</a><span class="sysop-show">&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Pawiak&amp;action=protect">protect</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Pawiak&amp;action=delete">delete</a></span>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Whatlinkshere/Andrew_Pawiak&amp;limit=999">links</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Andrew_Pawiak&amp;action=watch">watch</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Log&amp;page=Andrew+Pawiak">logs</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="//tools.wmflabs.org/pageviews?pages=Andrew_Pawiak&amp;project=en.wikipedia.org">views</a>)</span> – (<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Andrew_Pawiak" title="Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Andrew Pawiak">View AfD</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <span class="plainlinks"><a class="external text" href="https://tools.wmflabs.org/jackbot/snottywong/cgi-bin/votecounter.cgi?page=Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Andrew_Pawiak">Stats</a></span>)</dd>
<dd>(<span class="plainlinks"><i>Find sources:</i>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?as_eq=wikipedia&amp;q=%22Andrew+Pawiak%22">Google</a> (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?tbs=bks:1&amp;q=%22Andrew+Pawiak%22+-wikipedia">books</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?tbm=nws&amp;q=%22Andrew+Pawiak%22+-wikipedia">news</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?&amp;q=%22Andrew+Pawiak%22+site:news.google.com/newspapers&amp;source=newspapers">newspapers</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//scholar.google.com/scholar?q=%22Andrew+Pawiak%22">scholar</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/search?safe=off&amp;tbs=sur:fmc&amp;tbm=isch&amp;q=%22Andrew+Pawiak%22+-site:wikipedia.org+-site:wikimedia.org">free images</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/custom?hl=en&amp;cx=007734830908295939403%3Agalkqgoksq0&amp;cof=FORID%3A13%3BAH%3Aleft%3BCX%3AWikipedia%2520Reference%2520Search&amp;q=%22Andrew+Pawiak%22">WP refs</a>)&#160;<b>·</b> <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Free_English_newspaper_sources">FENS</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/action/doBasicSearch?Query=%22Andrew+Pawiak%22&amp;acc=on&amp;wc=on">JSTOR</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.nytimes.com/search/%22Andrew+Pawiak%22">NYT</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://wikipedialibrary.wmflabs.org/partners/">TWL</a></span>)</dd></dl>
<p>Article about footballer who hasn't played in a fully-pro league. All of the online coverage appears to be routine (database entries, match reports or transfer announcements) except for a couple of brief mentions in the Newcastle Herald (i.e., local coverage) noting that he was an unused substitute for the local club twice in the <a href="/wiki/A-League" title="A-League">A-League</a>. PROD was removed without explanation. <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 20:23, 12 August 2019 (UTC)
</p>

<dd><small class="delsort-notice">Note: This discussion has been included in the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Deletion_sorting/Australia" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Deletion sorting/Australia">list of Australia-related deletion discussions</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:Shellwood" title="User:Shellwood">Shellwood</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Shellwood" title="User talk:Shellwood">talk</a>) 20:29, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</small></dd></dl>
<ul><li><b>Keep</b> <span class="template-ping">@<a href="/wiki/User:GiantSnowman" title="User:GiantSnowman">GiantSnowman</a>:</span> - the <a href="/wiki/Philippines_Football_League" title="Philippines Football League">Philippines Football League</a> is in the list of fully pro leagues. even though the article states he made zero appearances there, he actually made at least one (see <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://sports.abs-cbn.com/football/news/2017/06/26/jpv-stuns-global-seizes-top-spot-davao-ilocos-end-draw-27865">1</a> and <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://businessmirror.com.ph/2017/06/26/japanese-odawara-strikes-twice-for-marikina/">2</a>). Thanks, <a href="/wiki/User:Das_osmnezz" title="User:Das osmnezz">Das osmnezz</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Das_osmnezz" title="User talk:Das osmnezz">talk</a>) 16:57, 13 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>Thank you. I stand corrected that Pawiak made 1 appearance in the fully-pro Philippines top division. That said, the only coverage I was able to find was that he "rattled the crossbar" with a shot during his club's scoreless draw with Davao. The article doesn't satisfy the GNG in my view, so it fails the spirit NFOOTBALL (see e.g., <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Phakamani_Mngadi" title="Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Phakamani Mngadi">Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Phakamani Mngadi</a>). <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 18:34, 13 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li><span class="template-ping">@<a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a>:</span>, If all articles that met <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NFOOTBALL" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NFOOTBALL">WP:NFOOTBALL</a> had to meet <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a>, a lot would have to be deleted since they have few sources; for example, the Russian Professional Football League players who all have a page (e.g. <a href="/wiki/Aleksandr_Maslov_(footballer,_born_2001)" title="Aleksandr Maslov (footballer, born 2001)">Aleksandr Maslov</a>). Thanks, <a href="/wiki/User:Das_osmnezz" title="User:Das osmnezz">Das osmnezz</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Das_osmnezz" title="User talk:Das osmnezz">talk</a>) 04:42, 15 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>All articles on footballers should be able to satisfy the GNG as NFOOTBALL is merely a presumption of notability. We generally expect sources to exist unless someone rebuts the presumption. Pawiak is a footballer working in places like Australia and the Philippines during the internet era so it ought to be pretty easily to find significant coverage, yet we really can't. <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 13:36, 15 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li>
<li><b>Delete</b> no fully pro play.<a href="/wiki/User:Johnpacklambert" title="User:Johnpacklambert">John Pack Lambert</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Johnpacklambert" title="User talk:Johnpacklambert">talk</a>) 00:32, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> - fails <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a> and <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NFOOTBALL" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NFOOTBALL">WP:NFOOTBALL</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:GiantSnowman" title="User:GiantSnowman">Giant</a><a href="/wiki/User_talk:GiantSnowman" title="User talk:GiantSnowman">Snowman</a> 09:10, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> per nom. No wide coverage. Sorely fails <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NFOOTBALL" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NFOOTBALL">WP:NFOOTBALL</a> and <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a>. -<a href="/wiki/User:AuthorAuthor" title="User:AuthorAuthor">AuthorAuthor</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:AuthorAuthor" title="User talk:AuthorAuthor">talk</a>) 18:18, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Keep</b> passes <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NFOOTY" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NFOOTY">WP:NFOOTY</a> and player is only 23 years and currently playing and there is some local coverage about him <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.newcastleherald.com.au/story/4641991/pawiak-takes-up-overseas-contract/">[1]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.newcastleherald.com.au/story/4544287/magpies-recruit-meets-jets-with-no-regrets/">[2]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.newcastleherald.com.au/story/5986885/npl-andrew-pawiak-back-on-solid-ground-with-lambton-after-turbulent-time/">[3]</a>.<a href="/wiki/User:Pharaoh_of_the_Wizards" title="User:Pharaoh of the Wizards">Pharaoh of the Wizards</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Pharaoh_of_the_Wizards" title="User talk:Pharaoh of the Wizards">talk</a>) 19:09, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> – 1 FPL appearance isn't a reason to keep. The links above all come from the same source (Newcastle Herald), so they're not independent of each other; they count as one GNG source for me and we need multiple. If the player were playing in an FPL, I would normally !vote draftify, but in this case, after the one FPL appearance two years ago, the player has been playing semi-professional ball, so there is no reason to think they will become notable in the next six months. Without two GNG sources or reason to think a second one will be written in the next six months, my !vote is delete. <span style="white-space:nowrap;">– <a href="/wiki/User:Levivich" title="User:Levivich">Leviv</a><span style="display:inline-block;position:relative;transform:rotate(45deg);bottom:-.57em;"><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Levivich" title="User talk:Levivich">ich</a></span></span> 19:50, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> Fails <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a>, and I'm not convinced Philippines have a fully professional league either - it's kind of in turmoil, is it not? <a href="/wiki/User:SportingFlyer" title="User:SportingFlyer">SportingFlyer</a> <i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:top;"><a href="/wiki/User_talk:SportingFlyer" title="User talk:SportingFlyer">T</a></span></i>·<i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:bottom;"><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer" title="Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer">C</a></span></i> 01:20, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>

<p>Article about footballer who hasn't played in a fully-pro league (he played in the <a href="/wiki/TT_Pro_League" title="TT Pro League">TT Pro League</a>, but a recent discussion at <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:FPL" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:FPL">WP:FPL</a> concluded that the sourcing was insufficient to demonstrate the league's asserted full professionalism). All of the online coverage appears to be routine (database entries, match reports or transfer announcements). PROD was removed without explanation. <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 19:58, 12 August 2019 (UTC)
</p>

<ul><li><b>Delete</b>. Classic <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:LISTCRUFT" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:LISTCRUFT">WP:LISTCRUFT</a>. Predominantly unsourced. <a href="/wiki/User:Ajf773" title="User:Ajf773">Ajf773</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Ajf773" title="User talk:Ajf773">talk</a>) 20:09, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Note:</b> The rationale for this list is stated on the talk page. It was made in 2013 from <a href="/w/index.php?title=Category:Fictional_heirs_apparent_who_never_acceded&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Category:Fictional heirs apparent who never acceded (page does not exist)">Category:Fictional heirs apparent who never acceded</a>, which was created in 2012 by <a href="/wiki/User:Andrei_Iosifovich" title="User:Andrei Iosifovich">Andrei&#160;Iosifovich</a>&#160;(<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Andrei_Iosifovich" title="User talk:Andrei Iosifovich">talk</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/Andrei_Iosifovich" title="Special:Contributions/Andrei Iosifovich">contribs</a>). The category was converted to a list before deletion per consensus at <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Categories_for_discussion/Log/2013_August_1#Category:Fictional_heirs_apparent_who_never_acceded" title="Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2013 August 1">Wikipedia:Categories for discussion/Log/2013 August 1#Category:Fictional heirs apparent who never acceded</a>.</li></ul>
<dl><dd>For the record, as the page name is not fully self-explanatory, the intro is as follows: <small>This is a list of <a href="/wiki/Fictional_character" class="mw-redirect" title="Fictional character">fictional characters</a> who were legally <b><a href="/wiki/Heir_apparent" title="Heir apparent">heirs apparent</a></b>, but never acceded to the throne or title to which they were entitled. This may be because they died before inheriting it, the throne was abolished, a usurper took the inheritance, or they simply chose not assert their birthright. While claiming a birthright can be a powerful motif in literature, some stories instead draw upon the tragedy or frustration of not being able to claim a title to which a character seemed destined to succeed.</small> – <a href="/wiki/User:Fayenatic_london" title="User:Fayenatic london">Fayenatic</a> <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Fayenatic_london" title="User talk:Fayenatic london"><b><span style="color: #FF0000;">L</span></b>ondon</a> 21:03, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</dd></dl>
<ul><li><b>Delete</b> Sorry, but this is completely everything wikipedia is not in my opinion. Not to mention failing <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:Govvy" title="User:Govvy">Govvy</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Govvy" title="User talk:Govvy">talk</a>) 21:56, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> - The majority of the information contained in this list is un-sourced, and while there may be sources found on some of the individual entries on the list, there are none that actually talk about the concept or grouping as a whole to show any sort of notability to the topic. As such, it pretty much fails <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:LISTN" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:LISTN">WP:LISTN</a>, along with being pure cruft. <a href="/wiki/User:Rorshacma" title="User:Rorshacma">Rorshacma</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Rorshacma" title="User talk:Rorshacma">talk</a>) 22:16, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> per nom. Nobody, but nobody (except Fayenatic), goes around wondering about such an obscure set of criteria. <a href="/wiki/User:Clarityfiend" title="User:Clarityfiend">Clarityfiend</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Clarityfiend" title="User talk:Clarityfiend">talk</a>) 05:43, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> While a list of real-world people with this attribute can be appropriate (and exists within <a href="/wiki/Heir_apparent" title="Heir apparent">Heir apparent</a>), this is an arbitrary and in-universe subset of characters. Wholly implausible that anyone would search this. –<a href="/wiki/User:LaundryPizza03" title="User:LaundryPizza03"><b style="color:#77b">Laundry</b><b style="color:#fb0">Pizza</b><b style="color:#b00">03</b></a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:LaundryPizza03" title="User talk:LaundryPizza03"><span style="color:#0d0">d</span></a><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/LaundryPizza03" title="Special:Contributions/LaundryPizza03"><span style="color:#0bf">c̄</span></a>) 07:34, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> - Bizarrely specific category. <a href="/wiki/User:Cosmic_Sans" title="User:Cosmic Sans">Cosmic Sans</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Cosmic_Sans" title="User talk:Cosmic Sans">talk</a>) 18:23, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>

<p>advertisement, and probably not notable. the large $ figures cited are not the size of its own investments, but the size of total investments by much larger investment companies in firms in which this rather insignificant company has invested quite small amounts.

The references otherwise are mere notices. <b><a href="/wiki/User:DGG" title="User:DGG"> DGG</a></b> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:DGG" title="User talk:DGG"> talk </a>) 19:03, 12 August 2019 (UTC) � <b><a href="/wiki/User:DGG" title="User:DGG"> DGG</a></b> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:DGG" title="User talk:DGG"> talk </a>) 19:03, 12 August 2019 (UTC)

<ul><li><b>Delete</b>. As per the previous AfD at which it was deleted: 'Run-of-the-mill venture capital company. Notability isn't inherited and therefore the companies they invested in do not confer notability on the investment firm. Wikipedia is not a directory or yellow pages. None of the references meet the criteria for establishing notability. Topic fails GNG and WP:NCORP'. This current article, though not blatant advertising, was tagged as promotional on creation but the author has done nothing to address the issues. The prose is clearly in the style in which a company would write about itself such as, for example, in a press release, and has the hallmarks of a commissioned work . <a href="/wiki/User:Kudpung" title="User:Kudpung">Kudpung กุดผึ้ง</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kudpung" title="User talk:Kudpung">talk</a>) 22:22, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li>

<dl><dd><dl><dd>Hawaii is located thousands of miles away from other landmasses. What do you expect? The state’s largest newspaper and the state’s biggest TV station are in Oahu and they have covered it. A major news outlet in Maui covered it as well. Therefore, I think your characterization is misleading. Do you think a news source that is not located in the state of Hawaii must report on it? I say keep it. <a href="/wiki/User:Jasonagastrich" title="User:Jasonagastrich">Jasonagastrich</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jasonagastrich" title="User talk:Jasonagastrich">talk</a>) 03:01, 6 August 2019 (UTC)</dd></dl></dd>

<ul><li>What would evidence of notability look like to you for a notable health food store chain in Hawaii? <a href="/wiki/User:Jasonagastrich" title="User:Jasonagastrich">Jasonagastrich</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jasonagastrich" title="User talk:Jasonagastrich">talk</a>) 20:27, 14 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>The same as for any other business in any other state - sustained coverage in reliable independent sources that not mainly local. <a href="/wiki/User:Mccapra" title="User:Mccapra">Mccapra</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Mccapra" title="User talk:Mccapra">talk</a>) 21:34, 15 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>I am uncertain whether or not that is a fair and legitimate criteria because Hawaii is separated from landmasses by thousands of miles. It is one thing to expect a Los Angeles-based health food chain to be covered by the New York Times, but it is quite another thing to expect a Hawaii-based health food chain to be covered by the Los Angeles Times. Be that as it may the largest newspaper and the largest TV news station in Hawaii along with other smaller media outlets have covered Down to Earth. <a href="/wiki/User:Jasonagastrich" title="User:Jasonagastrich">Jasonagastrich</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jasonagastrich" title="User talk:Jasonagastrich">talk</a>) 20:47, 18 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul>

<dd><small class="delsort-notice">Note: This discussion has been included in the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Deletion_sorting/Pennsylvania" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Deletion sorting/Pennsylvania">list of Pennsylvania-related deletion discussions</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:Icewhiz" title="User:Icewhiz">Icewhiz</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Icewhiz" title="User talk:Icewhiz">talk</a>) 18:17, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</small></dd></dl>
<ul><li><b>Delete</b> being an uncle by marriage of a future president of the US does not make one notable, unless you get lots of coverage for being such, which Musser didn't.<a href="/wiki/User:Johnpacklambert" title="User:Johnpacklambert">John Pack Lambert</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Johnpacklambert" title="User talk:Johnpacklambert">talk</a>) 00:33, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b>. While being a relative of the president may be plausible grounds for SIGCOV existing, in this case in my BEFORE I see mainly genealogy books, brief mentions of the marriage to aunt, brief mentions of a creamery job (Musser was the foreman) for Eisenhower's dad in 1892, and what I see in <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://books.google.co.il/books?id=g72pCgAAQBAJ&amp;pg=PT26&amp;dq=%22Christian+O.+Musser%22&amp;hl=en&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=0ahUKEwi36s77lYDkAhXoSxUIHeQfBYYQ6AEILjAB#v=onepage&amp;q=Musser&amp;f=false">Eisenhower: A Soldier's Life</a> does not seem sufficient for a standalone bio. <a href="/wiki/User:Icewhiz" title="User:Icewhiz">Icewhiz</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Icewhiz" title="User talk:Icewhiz">talk</a>) 15:40, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> per <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NOTINHERITED" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NOTINHERITED">WP:NOTINHERITED</a>. Relatives of a POTUS are included where (a) they helped raise, employ, or teach the future president, and/or (b) made a contribution/inspiration to the private side of such an important public figure, and/or (c) in whose home the famous forebear lived is now a national historic site. For example, many early Presidents were home-schooled by their father or other close relatives, were employed by a relative or close family friend, or otherwise made a meaningful impact in the life that helped the future Commander-in-Chief to start his path towards making history. <a href="/wiki/John_Adams,_Sr" class="mw-redirect" title="John Adams, Sr">John Adams, Sr</a> and <a href="/wiki/Madelyn_Dunham" title="Madelyn Dunham">Madelyn Dunham</a> come to mind. I don't see any of that here; some guy getting the president's dad a job once is too tenuous for me. <a href="/wiki/User:Bearian" title="User:Bearian">Bearian</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Bearian" title="User talk:Bearian">talk</a>) 19:38, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> -- obviously NN. <a href="/wiki/User:Peterkingiron" title="User:Peterkingiron">Peterkingiron</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Peterkingiron" title="User talk:Peterkingiron">talk</a>) 16:53, 17 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<div style="clear:both;"></div>
<dl><dd><i>The above discussion is preserved as an archive of the debate. <b style="color:red">Please do not modify it.</b> Subsequent comments should be made on the appropriate discussion page (such as the article's <a href="/wiki/Help:Using_talk_pages" class="mw-redirect" title="Help:Using talk pages">talk page</a> or in a <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Deletion_review" title="Wikipedia:Deletion review">deletion review</a>). No further edits should be made to this page.</i></dd></dl></div>
<p>All the citation are from independent news sources so WP:RS is not applicable. Moreover in awards and recognition section, there is indication of notability from high authority news sources.
</p>

No further edits should be made to this page.</i></dd></dl>

Not worthy of being included on <a href="/wiki/List_of_Marvel_Comics_characters:_S" title="List of Marvel Comics characters: S">List of Marvel Comics characters: S</a>, which is meant to be a repository for characters important within the fiction that do not meet GNG. I could not identify an appropriate redirect target. <a href="/wiki/User:Argento_Surfer" title="User:Argento Surfer">Argento Surfer</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Argento_Surfer" title="User talk:Argento Surfer">talk</a>) 15:17, 12 August 2019 (UTC)

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Romain_Carbonnier"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Romain_Carbonnier&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Romain Carbonnier (page does not exist)">Romain Carbonnier</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Romain_Carbonnier&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<dl><dd><span id="Romain_Carbonnier"></span><span class="plainlinks nourlexpansion lx"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Romain_Carbonnier&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Romain Carbonnier (page does not exist)">Romain Carbonnier</a> (<a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Romain_Carbonnier&amp;action=edit">edit</a>&#160;&#124; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Talk:Romain_Carbonnier&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Talk:Romain Carbonnier (page does not exist)">talk</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Romain_Carbonnier&amp;action=history">history</a><span class="sysop-show">&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Romain_Carbonnier&amp;action=protect">protect</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Romain_Carbonnier&amp;action=delete">delete</a></span>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Whatlinkshere/Romain_Carbonnier&amp;limit=999">links</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Romain_Carbonnier&amp;action=watch">watch</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Log&amp;page=Romain+Carbonnier">logs</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="//tools.wmflabs.org/pageviews?pages=Romain_Carbonnier&amp;project=en.wikipedia.org">views</a>)</span> – (<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Romain_Carbonnier" title="Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Romain Carbonnier">View AfD</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <span class="plainlinks"><a class="external text" href="https://tools.wmflabs.org/jackbot/snottywong/cgi-bin/votecounter.cgi?page=Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Romain_Carbonnier">Stats</a></span>)</dd>
<dd>(<span class="plainlinks"><i>Find sources:</i>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?as_eq=wikipedia&amp;q=%22Romain+Carbonnier%22">Google</a> (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?tbs=bks:1&amp;q=%22Romain+Carbonnier%22+-wikipedia">books</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?tbm=nws&amp;q=%22Romain+Carbonnier%22+-wikipedia">news</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?&amp;q=%22Romain+Carbonnier%22+site:news.google.com/newspapers&amp;source=newspapers">newspapers</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//scholar.google.com/scholar?q=%22Romain+Carbonnier%22">scholar</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/search?safe=off&amp;tbs=sur:fmc&amp;tbm=isch&amp;q=%22Romain+Carbonnier%22+-site:wikipedia.org+-site:wikimedia.org">free images</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/custom?hl=en&amp;cx=007734830908295939403%3Agalkqgoksq0&amp;cof=FORID%3A13%3BAH%3Aleft%3BCX%3AWikipedia%2520Reference%2520Search&amp;q=%22Romain+Carbonnier%22">WP refs</a>)&#160;<b>·</b> <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Free_English_newspaper_sources">FENS</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/action/doBasicSearch?Query=%22Romain+Carbonnier%22&amp;acc=on&amp;wc=on">JSTOR</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.nytimes.com/search/%22Romain+Carbonnier%22">NYT</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://wikipedialibrary.wmflabs.org/partners/">TWL</a></span>)</dd></dl>
<p>Article about former footballer who made a <b>2-minute</b> substitute's appearance in France's fully-pro <a href="/wiki/Ligue_2" title="Ligue 2">Ligue 2</a>, plus a handful (I haven't been able to find proof of an appearance, but an article indicates he and three other international players made no more than 10 appearances each) of appearances in South Africa's fully-pro <a href="/wiki/Premier_Soccer_League" title="Premier Soccer League">Premier Soccer League</a>. Although this appears to satisfy the bright-line of <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NFOOTBALL" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NFOOTBALL">WP:NFOOTBALL</a>, it does not because there is longstanding consensus that a footballer who played a minimal amount in a fully-pro league but comprehensively fails <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a> does not actually satisfy NFOOTBALL (see e.g., <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Phakamani_Mngadi" title="Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Phakamani Mngadi">Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Phakamani Mngadi</a>). All of the online coverage in French- and English-language sources appear to be routine (database entries or transfer announcements). <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 14:51, 12 August 2019 (UTC)
</p>

<li><b>Delete</b>. Fails <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a>. Regards, <a href="/wiki/User:Comte0" title="User:Comte0">Comte0</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Comte0" title="User talk:Comte0">talk</a>) 18:08, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li>

Our inclusion criteria for footballers are currently too broad at present.<a href="/wiki/User:Johnpacklambert" title="User:Johnpacklambert">John Pack Lambert</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Johnpacklambert" title="User talk:Johnpacklambert">talk</a>) 00:52, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Keep</b> - at least four appearances in FPL (meeting <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NFOOTBALL" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NFOOTBALL">WP:NFOOTBALL</a>) and enough coverage out there for me to be comfortable keeping. Needs improving, not deleting. <a href="/wiki/User:GiantSnowman" title="User:GiantSnowman">Giant</a><a href="/wiki/User_talk:GiantSnowman" title="User talk:GiantSnowman">Snowman</a> 09:11, 13 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>You are correct that Carbonnier also made 3 appearances in the league for Ajax Cape Town per <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.espnfc.com/player/105728/romain-carbonnier">espnfc.com</a>, but I'm concerned about the lack of local coverage of his time with the club (all of it is passing mentions - none flattering). I don't see how this article would satisfy the GNG. <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 14:34, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></li>
<li><b>Delete</b> – doesn't meet GNG, just brief mentions and routine game reports <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.kickoff.com/news/articles/south-africa-news/categories/news/news/ajax-boosted-by-new-signings/516569">[4]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.iol.co.za/capeargus/sport/french-striker-cleared-for-ajax-duty-599827">[5]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.goal.com/en/news/1659/south-africa/2009/04/07/1196580/carbonnier-set-for-ajax-cape-town-derby-debut">[6]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.pressreader.com/south-africa/cape-times/20090318/281913064030087">[7]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://ewn.co.za/2009/03/03/Duo-sign-for-Ajax">[8]</a>. I did get a kick out of <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.kickoff.com/news/articles/south-africa-news/categories/news/news/do-we-really-need-five-foreigners/520813">this</a> (<style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r886049556">.mw-parser-output .inline-quote-talk{font-family:Georgia,"DejaVu Serif",serif;color:#008560;quotes:none}.mw-parser-output .inline-quote-talk-italic{font-family:inherit;font-style:italic}.mw-parser-output .inline-quote-talk-marks{quotes:"\"""\""}</style><q class="inline-quote-talk">What has Mohammed Diallo (Ivory Coast) brought to Ajax Cape Town? What did the four they signed last season offer? ...&#160;Romain Carbonnier (France), nothing to write home about really… none played 10 games. All have a single thing in common; they have all left the team after just a season!</q>) and <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.iol.co.za/capeargus/sport/getting-to-the-root-of-why-ajax-have-slumped-600810">this</a> (<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r886049556"/><q class="inline-quote-talk">With Ajax skipper Brett Evans suspended, influential winger Franklin Cale injured, and coach Craig Rosslee resting a few regular players, squad members like&#160;... Frenchman Romain Carbonnier&#160;... played a part during some stage of yesterday's 90 minutes. And they failed dismally&#160;... In&#160;... Carbonnier&#160;...&#160;, Ajax have simply wasted their foreign quota.</q>). Query: can an article subject be notable for not being notable? <abbr title="Smiling face" style="border-bottom: none;"><img alt="Face-smile.svg" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Face-smile.svg/18px-Face-smile.svg.png" decoding="async" width="18" height="18" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Face-smile.svg/27px-Face-smile.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/79/Face-smile.svg/36px-Face-smile.svg.png 2x" data-file-width="48" data-file-height="48" /></abbr> <span style="white-space:nowrap;">– <a href="/wiki/User:Levivich" title="User:Levivich">Leviv</a><span style="display:inline-block;position:relative;transform:rotate(45deg);bottom:-.57em;"><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Levivich" title="User talk:Levivich">ich</a></span></span> 19:10, 13 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>I do think a footballer can be notable for widely-publicized poor play, but the minimal coverage of Carbonnier doesn't suggest he was a focus of the media or fans (he was just one of a batch of infrequently-used and underperforming international players on Ajax CT). I would need to see much more coverage to believe it passes the GNG. <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 20:22, 13 August 2019 (UTC)
<dl><dd>Good point, I'm reminded of <a href="/wiki/Bill_Buckner" title="Bill Buckner">Bill Buckner</a>. <span style="white-space:nowrap;">– <a href="/wiki/User:Levivich" title="User:Levivich">Leviv</a><span style="display:inline-block;position:relative;transform:rotate(45deg);bottom:-.57em;"><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Levivich" title="User talk:Levivich">ich</a></span></span> 00:11, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</dd></dl></li></ul></li>
<li><b>Keep</b> I actually think the sources provided by Levivich, along with the sources in the article, pass <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a>, especially the iol.co.za article and the goal.com article. He did appear in more games in France than the article currently shows. One potential source just says "Gone" <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.leparisien.fr/val-d-oise-95/franconville-change-de-braquet-26-06-2008-3298590295.php">[9]</a>... <a href="/wiki/User:SportingFlyer" title="User:SportingFlyer">SportingFlyer</a> <i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:top;"><a href="/wiki/User_talk:SportingFlyer" title="User talk:SportingFlyer">T</a></span></i>·<i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:bottom;"><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer" title="Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer">C</a></span></i> 01:34, 14 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>The <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.lfp.fr/joueur/carbonnier-romain/carriere">Ligue de Football Professionnel</a> records a single 2' Ligue 2 appearance for Carbonnier, and they are the most reliable source on Ligue 1 and Ligue 2 appearances from the 2000s and later. <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 03:56, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li>Also, that La Parisien article covers his time with amateurs Franconville - he played in the Coupe de France with them, but it's still amateur football. <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 04:00, 14 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>The "most reliable source" does not include his appearances for Ajaccio <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://sport.bild.de/fussball/co72/ligue-2/ma2105951/angers-sco_ac-ajaccio/aufstellung/">[10]</a> and at least the Clermont-Ajaccio cup match (cannot find a lineup though), and the South African league is also professional - the 2' would be relevant if he never played in another professional match and there wasn't anything we could write on him, but that's not the case here. Thanks for looking into the La Parisien article, I couldn't get it to load. <a href="/wiki/User:SportingFlyer" title="User:SportingFlyer">SportingFlyer</a> <i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:top;"><a href="/wiki/User_talk:SportingFlyer" title="User talk:SportingFlyer">T</a></span></i>·<i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:bottom;"><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer" title="Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer">C</a></span></i> 04:06, 14 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>I stand corrected (again). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.corsefootball.fr/aca/historique/2007-2008/">Corse Football</a> (a blog, but a reliable one for clubs AJ Ajaccio) has him making a single substitute's appearance against Angers SC in Ligue 2 during 2007. The Coupe de Ligue match was against amateurs Clermont, and is effectively a friendly. I added the appearance to the article's infobox, but it really changes very little as far as establishing notability or passing the GNG. <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 04:29, 14 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>I mean, we're going to disagree here - I think the African articles show he passes both <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NFOOTY" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NFOOTY">WP:NFOOTY</a> and <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a> and is eligible for an article, and this is a more substantial career than some of the technical <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NFOOTY" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NFOOTY">WP:NFOOTY</a> passes we end up deleting - but just to make an additional correction: Clermont finished 5th in the fully professional Ligue 2 the season of the league cup match (and Ajaccio 9th), equivalent to the English League Cup with the winner receiving a UEFA Cup qualification spot, so Clermont are neither amateurs, nor was the game effectively a friendly. <a href="/wiki/User:SportingFlyer" title="User:SportingFlyer">SportingFlyer</a> <i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:top;"><a href="/wiki/User_talk:SportingFlyer" title="User talk:SportingFlyer">T</a></span></i>·<i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:bottom;"><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer" title="Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer">C</a></span></i> 04:51, 14 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>I'm sorry; I rushed to the conclusion that Clermont were amateurs because they were competing in Championnat National during 2007. However, you're right that they achieved promotion to Ligue 2 before the Coupe de Ligue match in question. Still, Carbonnier's 3 competitive substitute's appearances with Ligue 2 clubs total less than 40 minutes - so let's keep that in perspective. <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 21:19, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li>
<li><b>Delete</b>. I do not agree that <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.iol.co.za/capeargus/sport/french-striker-cleared-for-ajax-duty-599827">[11]</a> and <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.goal.com/en/news/1659/south-africa/2009/04/07/1196580/carbonnier-set-for-ajax-cape-town-derby-debut">[12]</a> amount to significant coverage. The "in detail" requirement just isn't there. Yes, Charbonnier is mentioned in the headlines, but each article swiftly moves from routine news about him to other unrelated matters about the team. The handful of league appearances are close to irrelevant in the absence of significant coverage. And on an intuitive point: the article says he "is last known to have played for FC Montceau Bourgogne". If no-one knows where his career ended up, he can't really have been that notable. Significant coverage really means a global overview of a player's career; otherwise we can't have a biography and need to make silly statements like "is last known...". --<a href="/wiki/User:Mkativerata" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Mkativerata">Mkativerata</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Mkativerata" title="User talk:Mkativerata">talk</a>) 08:57, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> Lacks significant coverage, failing GNG <a href="/wiki/User:Taewangkorea" title="User:Taewangkorea">Taewangkorea</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Taewangkorea" title="User talk:Taewangkorea">talk</a>) 23:27, 17 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Miguel_Romeo"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Miguel_Romeo&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Miguel Romeo (page does not exist)">Miguel Romeo</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Miguel_Romeo&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<dl><dd><span id="Miguel_Romeo"></span><span class="plainlinks nourlexpansion lx"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Miguel_Romeo&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Miguel Romeo (page does not exist)">Miguel Romeo</a> (<a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Miguel_Romeo&amp;action=edit">edit</a>&#160;&#124; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Talk:Miguel_Romeo&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Talk:Miguel Romeo (page does not exist)">talk</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Miguel_Romeo&amp;action=history">history</a><span class="sysop-show">&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Miguel_Romeo&amp;action=protect">protect</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Miguel_Romeo&amp;action=delete">delete</a></span>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Whatlinkshere/Miguel_Romeo&amp;limit=999">links</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Miguel_Romeo&amp;action=watch">watch</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Log&amp;page=Miguel+Romeo">logs</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="//tools.wmflabs.org/pageviews?pages=Miguel_Romeo&amp;project=en.wikipedia.org">views</a>)</span> – (<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Miguel_Romeo" title="Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Miguel Romeo">View AfD</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <span class="plainlinks"><a class="external text" href="https://tools.wmflabs.org/jackbot/snottywong/cgi-bin/votecounter.cgi?page=Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Miguel_Romeo">Stats</a></span>)</dd>
<dd>(<span class="plainlinks"><i>Find sources:</i>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?as_eq=wikipedia&amp;q=%22Miguel+Romeo%22">Google</a> (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?tbs=bks:1&amp;q=%22Miguel+Romeo%22+-wikipedia">books</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?tbm=nws&amp;q=%22Miguel+Romeo%22+-wikipedia">news</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?&amp;q=%22Miguel+Romeo%22+site:news.google.com/newspapers&amp;source=newspapers">newspapers</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//scholar.google.com/scholar?q=%22Miguel+Romeo%22">scholar</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/search?safe=off&amp;tbs=sur:fmc&amp;tbm=isch&amp;q=%22Miguel+Romeo%22+-site:wikipedia.org+-site:wikimedia.org">free images</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/custom?hl=en&amp;cx=007734830908295939403%3Agalkqgoksq0&amp;cof=FORID%3A13%3BAH%3Aleft%3BCX%3AWikipedia%2520Reference%2520Search&amp;q=%22Miguel+Romeo%22">WP refs</a>)&#160;<b>·</b> <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Free_English_newspaper_sources">FENS</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/action/doBasicSearch?Query=%22Miguel+Romeo%22&amp;acc=on&amp;wc=on">JSTOR</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.nytimes.com/search/%22Miguel+Romeo%22">NYT</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://wikipedialibrary.wmflabs.org/partners/">TWL</a></span>)</dd></dl>
<p>Article about footballer who hasn't played in a fully-pro league (he played in the TT Pro League, but a recent discussion at <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:FPL" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:FPL">WP:FPL</a> concluded that the sourcing was insufficient to demonstrate the league's asserted full professionalism). All of the online coverage appears to be routine (database entries, match reports or transfer announcements). <a href="/wiki/User:Jogurney" title="User:Jogurney">Jogurney</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Jogurney" title="User talk:Jogurney">talk</a>) 14:08, 12 August 2019 (UTC)
</p>

<p>This is a person who is known for his involvement in one event, not to a scale which warrants his own bio. Any information not already covered at the appropriate event can be easily merged there. <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 14:03, 12 August 2019 (UTC)

<dl><dd><ul><li><b>Oppose</b>. 65-year-old immigrant single-handedly overpowering an active shooter is a badass hero, regardless of independent criteria-box-checking coverage which he has and will continue to get. First reactions of people I've seen hear the story are all about more details on him: diet, training, workout routine, etc. Details of his own life inappropriate to shooting page should have a home here. Obviously the dab should be better.&#160;—&#160;<a href="/wiki/User_talk:LlywelynII" title="User talk:LlywelynII"><span style="text-shadow:#BBBBBB 0.1em 0.1em 0.1em; class=texhtml">Llywelyn<span style="color: Gold;">II</span></span></a> 14:46, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li>By that standard, every "badass" old person who stops people in any old armed barfight deserves an article - but generally that barfight is not going to get an article itself! He's a pretty cool guy, but until coverage shifts to him over the web messages of the shooter (you'll see there's no <a href="/w/index.php?title=EndChan_messages_sent_by_Philip_Manshaus&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="EndChan messages sent by Philip Manshaus (page does not exist)">EndChan messages sent by Philip Manshaus</a> article...), he's not got enough for a bio. <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 14:53, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li>The problem is that you consider this a single event compared to a barfight while the person is considered a <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.tv2.no/a/10771562/">hero</a> in an extraordinary event in a peaceful country, an event with international scales that is rooted to <a href="/wiki/New_zealand_terrorist_attack" class="mw-redirect" title="New zealand terrorist attack">New Zealand Attack</a> and <a href="/wiki/El_Paso_shooting" class="mw-redirect" title="El Paso shooting">El Paso shooting</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:Sattar91" title="User:Sattar91">Sattar91</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Sattar91" title="User talk:Sattar91">talk</a>) 12:43, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li>In WP terms, it is. It is one event, in which one person stopped another from attacker others. You're looking too much at emotion rather than simple facts. Context can matter - specifically for the event, where the intentions of the attacker make it obviously very different to a barfight, but you want to establish notability on this man's actions, where he can be simply described as an unarmed man stopping an armed assailant. You can call him a hero, the media can call him a hero, WP policy won't be swayed by emotive language. <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 16:19, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl>

<dl><dd><ul><li>All of the information is already in that article. <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 18:53, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></dd></dl>
<ul><li><b>Oppose</b> This is not an isolated event for a low-profile person. The incident has significant domestic/international dimensions and was extensively covered both for the event itself and also the central hero of that, which is Mohammad Rafiq. There are several standalone articles and interviews with this specific person (as referenced in the article), suggesting that he may be a notable subject by himself. The incident will remain in the historical memory of people and its hero will also be remembered for years to come. Therefore the subject will be independently notable as soon as he has been characterized as the one tackling the terrorist and taking him down. The person has been portrayed in multiple independent credible sources both in Norwegian and English, including but not limited to <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://uk.reuters.com/video/2019/08/11/meet-the-retiree-who-tackled-a-gunman-in?videoId=586254482">Reuters</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/av/world-europe-49311888/norway-mosque-shooting-mohammad-rafiq-tells-of-tackling-gunman">BBC</a> and <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/man-arrested-in-norway-mosque-attack-expressed-anti-immigrant-views-11565551738">Wall Street Journal</a>. It has been said that the attacker does not have an article to justify deleting this article. It seems that there is a tendency not to give space to terrorists in Wikipedia as New Zealand attacker also did not get an article, but I don't see this an excuse for removing a positive human being's article.<a href="/wiki/User:Sattar91" title="User:Sattar91">Sattar91</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Sattar91" title="User talk:Sattar91">talk</a>) 12:58, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li>Wikipedia doesn't care how good or bad someone is, it cares how independently notable someone is. It has space for as many 'bad people' bios as good, but the fact of the matter is that (at the moment) neither the attacker nor the 'hero' have any relevance outside of the one event and can be satisfactorily covered there. <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 13:05, 13 August 2019 (UTC) <b>ETA</b> and how is it not an isolated event for a low-profile person? Has he done anything else of note? Outside of this event is he known to the media at all? No and no. Anyone would be delusion to think otherwise. <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 16:23, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></dd></dl>

<td style="border: solid 1px Silver; padding: 0.6em; background: White;">
<dl><dd><dl><dd><ul><li>This person is independently notable now. Of course there is always a starting point, but then the world has a notable person forever given that the event possesses large enough dimensions. In this particular case I think the terrorist can have an article in Wikipedia too but I obviously can not bring up reasoning on why nobody started that yet. <a href="/wiki/Anders_Behring_Breivik" title="Anders Behring Breivik">Breivik</a>'s article is a clear instance for a person who became notable in one single event and remained notable afterwards. He will be always remembered as a negative character. Likewise, Rafiq will be always remembered, however as a positive character as a <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.berlingske.dk/europa/mohammed-rafiq-er-norges-nye-helt-men-ikke-alle-er-begejstrede">National Danish newspaper</a> writes: "Rafiq is Norway's new hero ...he acted instinctively and courageously and prevented a terror attack from developing. This is the opinion of Norwegian police, Prime Minister Erna Solberg and many other Norwegians".<a href="/wiki/User:Sattar91" title="User:Sattar91">Sattar91</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Sattar91" title="User talk:Sattar91">talk</a>) 13:29, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li>You have false expectations of Wikipedia. Every time I try to make the article neutral, you come and change it to worship the man. Wikipedia reports facts, it doesn't want to create a reverent praise song because you think the guy's the best. Without all the praise you are heaping on him, there is even less notability. You may really like him, and many people around you may be talking about nothing but him, cheering, wanting his autograph, but that doesn't make him notable in Wikipedia terms. So I feel for you, but I could name you my little old teacher who singlehandedly took down a kid trying to stab people and, guess what, she doesn't have an article. Hero to some, but widely unimportant. From your edits it appears you are too invested in this man and think too highly of him to understand or accept that he doesn't meet WP criteria. <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 13:40, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li>You're also not looking at how much bigger Breivik's attack was. 70-something people died, many children. He spent two hours spree shooting after bombing the capital. That's on a whole other scale to this attack. Some single events are massively notable. The events the news stops around the world for. 22/7 was one. This was not. <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 13:44, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li>Very nice point. The <b>size</b> of the events are different, but the natures are not. That only means that the <b>size</b> of the articles will be different spontaneously as a result. It will never mean that one of these events gets an article and the other one is just deemed irrelevant for WP.<a href="/wiki/User:Sattar91" title="User:Sattar91">Sattar91</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Sattar91" title="User talk:Sattar91">talk</a>) 14:31, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li>Both events have pages. But sizes of events also determine their global effect/impact and importance. <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 14:54, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li>Yes, both events have pages, but you keep saying that only one can have article for its character. Global effect/impact and importance? how do you judge that this person/event does not have that? <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://uk.reuters.com/video/2019/08/11/meet-the-retiree-who-tackled-a-gunman-in?videoId=586254482">Reuters</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.bbc.com/news/av/world-europe-49311888/norway-mosque-shooting-mohammad-rafiq-tells-of-tackling-gunman">BBC</a> and <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/man-arrested-in-norway-mosque-attack-expressed-anti-immigrant-views-11565551738">Wall Street Journal</a> and 20+ references that I have added and you did the favor of removing some of them. <a href="/wiki/2011_Norway_attacks" title="2011 Norway attacks">2011 Norway attacks</a> and <a href="/wiki/B%C3%A6rum_mosque_shooting" title="Bærum mosque shooting">Bærum mosque shooting</a> both have the same roots in <a href="/wiki/Islamofobia" class="mw-redirect" title="Islamofobia">Islamofobia</a> and <a href="/wiki/Far-right_extremism" class="mw-redirect" title="Far-right extremism">far-right extremism</a> and the characters of both events can have an article in WP given that they are covered extensively with multiple credible independent source.<a href="/wiki/User:Sattar91" title="User:Sattar91">Sattar91</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Sattar91" title="User talk:Sattar91">talk</a>) 15:40, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li>Being simply named in multiple RS is tantamount to "this exists, and media tells us this exists". There's no added notability since all the RS just repeat the same tale where 'X did Y one time' and nothing more of note - 100 RS with the same story, some down to the same wording, is no better than 5 RS. And that doesn't get a bio. If something more transpires of his 15 minutes of fame, like if there's a beautiful shift of media coverage of future attacks to not give details of attackers but look at victims' actions after this guy highlighted strength of resistance or something, or there's new legislation in Norway, or people planning attacks stop and release statements saying they were scared of being stopped by a badass old man, you can revisit making an article, but it's not widely notable atm. <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 16:13, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><ul><li>But in all events, this huge, all media will do the same, repeating 'X did Y and Z was the aftermath'. Repeating, per se, does not void the credibility/notability of the event nor its characters. I still did not get the answer to this simple question: what is the difference between the characters in Breivik's story and Bærum shooting, other than the size of killing? Nobody knew Breivik before the incident, so it was a single event, made him (in)famous. The root cause for both act of terror are the same, the motives are the same, the terminology utilized by the perpetrators before committing the act are almost identical, the type of weapons are similar, but the number of innocent human beings murdered are different: so will be the size of the articles for the events and their characters.<a href="/wiki/User:Sattar91" title="User:Sattar91">Sattar91</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Sattar91" title="User talk:Sattar91">talk</a>) 08:11, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl>
</td></tr></tbody></table></div>

Unless news coverage of an individual goes beyond the context of a single event, our coverage of that individual should be limited to the article about that event, in proportion to their importance to the overall topic." <a href="/wiki/User:Kingsif" title="User:Kingsif">Kingsif</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Kingsif" title="User talk:Kingsif">talk</a>) 16:43, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>

<p>This article asserts a medical diagnosis based on a small number of primary sources, most of which are not medical, which use different terms. This is not distinct from anxiety due to any other cause, as far as I can see. As-is, this looks to me like <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:SYN" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:SYN">WP:SYN</a>. <b><a href="/wiki/User_talk:JzG" title="User talk:JzG">Guy</a></b> <small>(<a href="/wiki/User:JzG/help" title="User:JzG/help">Help!</a>)</small> 12:37, 12 August 2019 (UTC)
</p>

<dd>It is not a mental health effect of climate change, it is a mental health problem that leads to irrational beliefs about the climate. --<a href="/wiki/User:Mfb" title="User:Mfb">mfb</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Mfb" title="User talk:Mfb">talk</a>) 08:34, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<ul><li><b>Redirect</b>, this seems to be an article about a single case over a decade ago that fits into the general category of <a href="/wiki/Eco-anxiety" title="Eco-anxiety">Eco-anxiety</a>. It's worth noting that the <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Climate_psychosis&amp;oldid=910397778">original version</a> of the article(from two days ago) was about two sentences of coverage of that one unique case before launching into a *much* more dubious discussion that borders on climate change denial. If this article is kept, it should be watched carefully to make sure it doesn't become a home for fringe ideas. <a href="/wiki/User:ApLundell" title="User:ApLundell">ApLundell</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:ApLundell" title="User talk:ApLundell">talk</a>) 05:22, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Redirect or delete</b> - 200 Google hits for "Climate psychosis", not a common term but still used sometimes. --<a href="/wiki/User:Mfb" title="User:Mfb">mfb</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Mfb" title="User talk:Mfb">talk</a>) 08:34, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Redirect</b> as argued above. The current version of the article suffers from a mishmash of denialist and denial-ish sources, and is basically a grab-bag of uses of the word "psychosis". I'd call the last two sections <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:SYNTH" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:SYNTH">WP:SYNTH</a>, but I'm not sure they're coherent enough to qualify. <a href="/wiki/User:XOR%27easter" title="User:XOR&#39;easter">XOR&#39;easter</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:XOR%27easter" title="User talk:XOR&#39;easter">talk</a>) 15:37, 13 August 2019 (UTC)
<dl><dd>I wouldn't exactly weep buckets if it were <b>deleted</b>, either. There are basically two sources worth using <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://doi.org/10.1080%2F00048670701881603">[17]</a><a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.theage.com.au/national/a-climate-of-despair-20140811-102r1w.html">[18]</a>, and anything based on them could be rewritten from scratch with nominal effort, so keeping the page history available isn't necessary. <a href="/wiki/User:XOR%27easter" title="User:XOR&#39;easter">XOR&#39;easter</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:XOR%27easter" title="User talk:XOR&#39;easter">talk</a>) 17:54, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</dd></dl></li>
<li><b>Delete</b>. Most sources are useless propaganda, the term is used almost only by fringe proponents. --<a href="/wiki/User:Hob_Gadling" title="User:Hob Gadling">Hob Gadling</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Hob_Gadling" title="User talk:Hob Gadling">talk</a>) 16:28, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Redirect/delete</b> POVFork. Presenting the topic removed from the context of <a href="/wiki/Climate_change_denial" title="Climate change denial">climate change denial</a> and <a href="/wiki/Eco-anxiety" title="Eco-anxiety">eco-anxiety</a> has no place in a serious encyclopedia. I started going through the sources looking for something to salvage, but it looks futile. --<a href="/wiki/User:Ronz" title="User:Ronz">Ronz</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Ronz" title="User talk:Ronz">talk</a>) 17:39, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Redirect or delete</b> The lead is okay, and could almost bw merged with <a href="/wiki/Eco-anxiety" title="Eco-anxiety">eco-anxiety</a>, but everything after that is just a <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:COATRACK" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:COATRACK">WP:COATRACK</a> <span style="text-shadow:grey 0.118em 0.118em 0.118em; class=texhtml"><b><a href="/wiki/User:Adam_Cuerden" title="User:Adam Cuerden">Adam Cuerden</a></b> <sup>(<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Adam_Cuerden" title="User talk:Adam Cuerden">talk</a>)</sup><sub>Has about 6.9% of all <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:FP" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:FP">FPs</a></sub></span> 14:03, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>

<ul><li><b>Comment</b> <a href="/wiki/CIF_North_Coast_Section" title="CIF North Coast Section">CIF North Coast Section</a> is not a conference, per se. It's a high school sports administrative section of <a href="/wiki/Northern_California" title="Northern California">Northern California</a> with probably over 100 schools. While the current state of the lists might be <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:UGLY" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:UGLY">WP:UGLY</a> and lacking citations with independent sources, I'd be surprised if the newspapers from the cities of the various schools didn't talk about the championship grouping, which would satisy <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:LISTN" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:LISTN">WP:LISTN</a>: <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r886049556"/><q class="inline-quote-talk inline-quote-talk-marks">The entirety of the list does not need to be documented in sources for notability, only that the grouping or set in general has been.</q> This is distinguished from a standalone list about one high school conference, which would likely only have the city's local paper covering it.—<a href="/wiki/User:Bagumba" title="User:Bagumba">Bagumba</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Bagumba" title="User talk:Bagumba">talk</a>) 09:55, 28 July 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li>'<i>Probably delete<b> -- at worst </b></i><b>merge</b> to <a href="/wiki/CIF_North_Coast_Section" title="CIF North Coast Section">CIF North Coast Section</a>, if that is what it is about, which is far from clear. Is it is list of league champions by year? Nevertheless I would question whether a school basketball league is WP notable. <a href="/wiki/User:Peterkingiron" title="User:Peterkingiron">Peterkingiron</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Peterkingiron" title="User talk:Peterkingiron">talk</a>) 16:26, 30 July 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>

<ul><li><b>Delete</b> it's probably technically a <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NOTSTATS" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NOTSTATS">WP:NOTSTATS</a> failure, and if we keep it, will still be unsourced. If we can source it I don't mind if it's merged somewhere. <a href="/wiki/User:SportingFlyer" title="User:SportingFlyer">SportingFlyer</a> <i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:top;"><a href="/wiki/User_talk:SportingFlyer" title="User talk:SportingFlyer">T</a></span></i>·<i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:bottom;"><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer" title="Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer">C</a></span></i> 04:20, 15 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> generally we find that articles such as this one do not generate enough press to surpass <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a>. This discussion has been open long enough that any sources should have come to our attention by now. I'll admit that I do find some articles with mention <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.thepress.net/sports/north-coast-section-releases-soccer-and-basketball-playoff-brackets/article_49492946-2d8b-11e9-a9d9-23a00e927427.html">[19]</a>, <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.mercurynews.com/2019/02/10/ncs-basketball-playoffs-why-libertys-feeling-slighted/">[20]</a>, and <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.mercurynews.com/2019/02/21/ncs-ccs-basketball-wednesdays-surprises-trends-and-more/">[21]</a>. These articles are about specific games and tournaments, so <i>maybe</i> the organization itself could pass <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a>, but none of those articles are really about the <i>history</i> of the organization. So then it boils down to this for me: there seems to be no sources for the <i>history</i> of the organization, so this looks like <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:OR" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:OR">original research</a> or perhaps a case were someone is trying to use Wikipedia as a free web-hosting server. On those grounds, it definitely needs to go. I have no objection if the data can be sourced and then operationally it may be better to merge to <a href="/wiki/CIF_North_Coast_Section" title="CIF North Coast Section">CIF North Coast Section</a>.--<a href="/wiki/User:Paulmcdonald" title="User:Paulmcdonald">Paul McDonald</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Paulmcdonald" title="User talk:Paulmcdonald">talk</a>) 14:05, 19 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Christopher_Jobson"><a href="/wiki/Christopher_Jobson" class="mw-redirect" title="Christopher Jobson">Christopher Jobson</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Christopher_Jobson&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>

<p>A quick google search shows very little of this person or how notable he may be. I will let the community decide as i was a borderline decision of QD or AFD <a href="/wiki/User:10MB" title="User:10MB">10MB</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:10MB" title="User talk:10MB">talk</a>) 11:41, 12 August 2019 (UTC)
</p><p>Thanks for starting the discussion. I'm happy to go with whatever direction the community decides, but I will mention that the website he created has 10 million monthly readers and the breadth of references I included in the article span almost 8 years and include the National Endowment for the Arts, Fast Company, and the San Francisco Chronicle. Jobson--and his website--seem to have staying power. Within the art world he is very highly regarding. In fact, they included the blog in a Apple TV ad a few years ago.
</p><p>Thanks again, <a href="/wiki/User:Fullrabb" title="User:Fullrabb">Fullrabb</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Fullrabb" title="User talk:Fullrabb">talk</a>) 11:45, 12 August 2019 (UTC)Fullrabb

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Congregation_of_the_Heart_of_Mary"><a href="/wiki/Congregation_of_the_Heart_of_Mary" class="mw-redirect" title="Congregation of the Heart of Mary">Congregation of the Heart of Mary</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Congregation_of_the_Heart_of_Mary&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<dl><dd><span id="Congregation_of_the_Heart_of_Mary"></span><span class="plainlinks nourlexpansion lx"><a href="/wiki/Congregation_of_the_Heart_of_Mary" class="mw-redirect" title="Congregation of the Heart of Mary">Congregation of the Heart of Mary</a> (<a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Congregation_of_the_Heart_of_Mary&amp;action=edit">edit</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Congregation_of_the_Heart_of_Mary&amp;action=protect">protect</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Congregation_of_the_Heart_of_Mary&amp;action=delete">delete</a></span>&#160;&#124;
