<dl><dd><small class="delsort-notice">Note: This discussion has been included in the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Deletion_sorting/Bands_and_musicians" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Deletion sorting/Bands and musicians">list of Bands and musicians-related deletion discussions</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:Mccapra" title="User:Mccapra">Mccapra</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Mccapra" title="User talk:Mccapra">talk</a>) 04:53, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</small></dd>
<dd><small class="delsort-notice">Note: This discussion has been included in the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Deletion_sorting/Finland" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Deletion sorting/Finland">list of Finland-related deletion discussions</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:Mccapra" title="User:Mccapra">Mccapra</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Mccapra" title="User talk:Mccapra">talk</a>) 04:53, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</small></dd>
<dd><small class="delsort-notice">Note: This discussion has been included in the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Deletion_sorting/Music" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Deletion sorting/Music">list of Music-related deletion discussions</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:CAPTAIN_RAJU" title="User:CAPTAIN RAJU"><span style="font-family: Bradley Hand ITC;"><b>CAPTAIN RAJU</b></span></a><sup><a href="/wiki/User_talk:CAPTAIN_RAJU" title="User talk:CAPTAIN RAJU">(T)</a></sup> 04:54, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</small></dd></dl>
<ul><li><b>Keep</b> <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:BAND" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:BAND">WP:BAND</a> recommends notability for bands be judged by: "Has had a record certified gold or higher in at least one country" -- check (which presumably also satisifes the other criteria of "Has had a single or album on any country's national music chart"; "Has released two or more albums on a major record label or on one of the more important indie labels" -- The Finnish Wikipedia article on one of their albums <a class="external text" href="https://fi.wikipedia.org/wiki/Varjoja,_varkaita_ja_vanhoja_valokuvia_Osa_3">here</a> tells us it was released on EMI, other albums would need to be checked; "Has become one of the most prominent representatives of a notable style" -- it needs sourcing, but the article says "They are renowned for a distinguished style with heavy basement jazz influences." As for sources, the second page of a Google search on the band's name gives me <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://yle.fi/aihe/artikkeli/2013/09/16/sir-elwoodin-hiljaiset-varit-tarjoili-keskiolutjatsia-1990-luvun-varjoisissa">this</a> at <a href="/wiki/TV_Finland" title="TV Finland">TV Finland</a> and the third page <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.mtvuutiset.fi/artikkeli/sir-elwoodin-hiljaiset-varit/2838730">this</a> at <a href="/wiki/MTV_(Finnish_TV_channel)" title="MTV (Finnish TV channel)">MTV Finland</a>. It is also a well written article that it would be a shame to lose. -<a href="/wiki/User:Lopifalko" title="User:Lopifalko">Lopifalko</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Lopifalko" title="User talk:Lopifalko">talk</a>) 05:18, 12 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>I have added these sources to the article. -<a href="/wiki/User:Lopifalko" title="User:Lopifalko">Lopifalko</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Lopifalko" title="User talk:Lopifalko">talk</a>) 05:47, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></li>
<li><b>Keep</b>: lots of charting records in Finland, both singles and albums <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://finnishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Sir+Elwoodin+Hiljaiset+V%E4rit&amp;titel=Pahaa+verta&amp;cat=s">[26]</a>, two gold discs <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.ifpi.fi/tutkimukset-ja-tilastot/kulta-ja-platinalevyt/?q=Sir+Elwoodin+hiljaiset+v%C3%A4rit">[27]</a>... clearly a popular group in Finland and easily passes <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:BAND" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:BAND">WP:BAND</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:Richard3120" title="User:Richard3120">Richard3120</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Richard3120" title="User talk:Richard3120">talk</a>) 20:41, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><dl><dd><b>Additional comment</b>: I'd also add that they pass criterion 5 of WP:BAND as well... they were signed to EMI Records for 18 years, during their greatest period of success, and since 2010 they have been signed to a Finnish label which is a fully-owned subsidiary of Sony Music. With so many top 20 singles and albums over the last 30 years, it would be amazing if there weren't any print sources in Finnish, if not online ones. <a href="/wiki/User:Richard3120" title="User:Richard3120">Richard3120</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Richard3120" title="User talk:Richard3120">talk</a>) 21:23, 13 August 2019 (UTC)</dd></dl></dd></dl>
<ul><li><b>Keep</b> - In agreement with the previous voters. The article could use some improvement but the band has clearly had several charting records in their country and reliable media notice in that country's media. ---<span style="font-family: Calibri"><a href="/wiki/User:Doomsdayer520" title="User:Doomsdayer520"><b style="color: DarkOrchid"><small>DOOMSDAYER</small>520</b></a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Doomsdayer520" title="User talk:Doomsdayer520">Talk</a>&#124;<a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/Doomsdayer520" title="Special:Contributions/Doomsdayer520">Contribs</a>)</span> 17:11, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Keep</b> passes both criteria 2 and criteria 5 of <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NMUSIC" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NMUSIC">WP:NMUSIC</a> regards, <a href="/wiki/User:Atlantic306" title="User:Atlantic306">Atlantic306</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Atlantic306" title="User talk:Atlantic306">talk</a>) 18:12, 16 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>

<dd><small class="delsort-notice">Note: This discussion has been included in the <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:WikiProject_Deletion_sorting/People" title="Wikipedia:WikiProject Deletion sorting/People">list of People-related deletion discussions</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:Shellwood" title="User:Shellwood">Shellwood</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Shellwood" title="User talk:Shellwood">talk</a>) 15:17, 27 July 2019 (UTC)</small></dd></dl>
<ul><li><b>Delete</b> – Does not meet <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:BASIC" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:BASIC">WP:BASIC</a>, as per my previous nomination at <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/%C3%81ngel_Abrea_(2nd_nomination)" title="Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Ángel Abrea (2nd nomination)">Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Ángel Abrea (2nd nomination)</a>. No adequate evidence of notability was provided at that time. One source that might possibly provide significant coverage is not enough. <i>Multiple</i> independent reliable sources that provide significant coverage are required, not just one that may possibly have the required depth-of-coverage, or maybe not. Furthermore, there is no presumed notability for religious subjects on English Wikipedia. The subject may be important in the LDS church, but is not notable as per <i>Wikipedia's standards</i> of notability at this time. <span class="smallcaps" style="font-variant:small-caps;"><a href="/wiki/User:Northamerica1000" title="User:Northamerica1000">North America</a><sup><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Northamerica1000" title="User talk:Northamerica1000"><span style="font-size: x-small;">1000</span></a></sup></span> 17:40, 3 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>

<ul><li><b>KEEP</b> He is selected as a USA representative to the <a href="/wiki/2019_World_Athletics_Championships" title="2019 World Athletics Championships">World Championships</a> in a little over a month which will guarantee satisfying <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NATHLETE" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NATHLETE">WP:NATHLETE</a> and by being selected is not <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:CRYSTAL" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:CRYSTAL">WP:CRYSTAL</a> now. He is currently ranked #15 in the world which makes him a serious contender. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.iaaf.org/records/toplists/jumps/pole-vault/outdoor/men/senior/2019?regionType=world&amp;page=1&amp;bestResultsOnly=true">Here's the official list.</a> He has already represented the USA in <a href="/wiki/2018_IAAF_World_U20_Championships_%E2%80%93_Men%27s_pole_vault" title="2018 IAAF World U20 Championships – Men&#39;s pole vault">International competition</a>, <a href="/wiki/2019_NACAC_U23_Championships_in_Athletics" title="2019 NACAC U23 Championships in Athletics">twice</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.athleticsnacac.org/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/MEX-NACAC-U18U20-Queretaro-05-07JUL2019-RESULTS.pdf">[30]</a> coming away with a Silver Medal both times. Here's some news reporting <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://www.wbnq.com/2018/07/16/pole-vaulter-zach-bradford-wins-silver-at-iaaf-u20-championships-video/">[31]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="http://vaultermagazine.com/kansas-vaulters-break-facility-record-at-jayhawk-classic/">[32]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www2.ljworld.com/sports/2019/apr/20/lokedi-returns-to-ku-relays-in-emotional-1500-meter-run/">[33]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.kagstv.com/article/sports/fritsch-wins-gold-for-team-usa/499-551a5acd-a5dd-4c7f-bac5-aaa375aa7e27">[34]</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external autonumber" href="https://www.pantagraph.com/sports/high-school/track-and-field/bhs-star-bradford-to-pole-vault-for-kansas/article_b183b9bf-f0fd-5ebb-95d8-44c7f6a7e922.html">[35]</a> Each of those are reporting on different achievements through his relatively short career. I suggest this AfD be withdrawn. <a href="/wiki/User:Trackinfo" title="User:Trackinfo">Trackinfo</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Trackinfo" title="User talk:Trackinfo">talk</a>) 08:13, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</li>

<li><b>Comment</b>, the sources are all routine coverage of sporting events, not the in-depth coverage needed to meet <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a>, and still does not meet <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NATHLETE" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NATHLETE">WP:NATHLETE</a>.<a href="/wiki/User:Onel5969" title="User:Onel5969"><b><span style="color:#536895;">Onel</span><span style="color:#ffb300;">5969</span></b></a> <sup><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Onel5969" title="User talk:Onel5969"><i style="color:blue">TT me</i></a></sup> 23:54, 14 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><dl><dd>It frustrates me the depth to which some people will stoop in order to get deletion brownie points. Since you have chosen to misrepresent the sources lets analyze. WBNQ local source reports on local kid who wins a silver medal in international competition. They would not cover the competition if it were not for the local athlete. Zach Bradford is named in the headline. Vaulter, a sport specific website, reported on both he and teammate Hussain Al Hizam breaking the Kansas Indoor stadium record. Because of tie braking rules, he finished second in the competition but both get credit for the record. And might I point out the mere fact that they are talking about a record means it is not routine. LJWorld is the local paper in Lawrence, Kansas, where he now goes to the University. The headline Zach by name talking about the outdoor record he set, exclusively, breaking a 36 year old facility record. Not routine. KAGS, local TV station for Sam Houston State where his USA teammate Clayton Fritsch goes to school. Yes the article focused on Fritsch, local boy makes good again, but it also mentions Bradford, who jumped the same height . . . those tie breaking rules again . . . both dominating the other international athletes when he won the silver medal. Still not routine. And pantagraph is his Bloomington, Indiana hometown newspaper reporting when he signed to go to University of Kansas out of high school. His name again appears in the headline, local boy makes good, and is not routine. Now lets carry this a little further. Since you have continue to press the argument; you are wikilawyering the letter of <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NATHLETE" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NATHLETE">WP:NATHLETE</a>. If he had been on the favoring side of either of those silver medals, he's have an international junior gold and you'd have zero argument. He has already been selected to go to the World Championships. The moment he sets foot on that track he will fulfill the letter of <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:NATHLETE" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:NATHLETE">WP:NATHLETE</a> and this article will be back up. Even if he doesn't show up, there will be a story about that. In that month, as that competition comes closer, his name will show up in entry lists and dope sheets around the world. You are pressing to deny the journalists of the world easy data on this college sophomore, #4 American, coming in to the championships ranked #15. What is there to gain by pursuing this AfD, other than stupid deletionist brownie points? <a href="/wiki/User:Trackinfo" title="User:Trackinfo">Trackinfo</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Trackinfo" title="User talk:Trackinfo">talk</a>) 08:44, 15 August 2019 (UTC)</dd></dl></dd></dl>

<p>Tournament episodes of a game show. While <i><a href="/wiki/Jeopardy!" title="Jeopardy!">Jeopardy!</a></i> is a widely notable television show and part of pop culture, an unreferenced article about a week-long tournament every/every-other season does not meet <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:N" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:N">WP:N</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/search?q=jeopardy+teacher%27s+tournament&amp;oq=jeopardy+teacher%27s+tournament&amp;aqs=chrome..69i57.2804j0j0&amp;sourceid=chrome&amp;ie=UTF-8">Google search</a> produces promotional links from the <i>Jeopardy!</i> website and local news coverage of winner (which does not meet <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:SIGCOV" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:SIGCOV">WP:SIGCOV</a>), links back to this article and to the production website. Subject is adequately covered in <a href="/wiki/List_of_Jeopardy!_tournaments_and_events" title="List of Jeopardy! tournaments and events">List of Jeopardy! tournaments and events</a>. Only source in article is to confirm death of a contestant who earlier competed in the tournament. <a href="/wiki/User:AldezD" class="mw-redirect" title="User:AldezD">AldezD</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:AldezD" title="User talk:AldezD">talk</a>) 02:33, 12 August 2019 (UTC)
</p>

<ul><li><b>Delete</b> never a head coach. <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a> doesn't appear to be satisfied either. <a href="/wiki/User:SportingFlyer" title="User:SportingFlyer">SportingFlyer</a> <i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:top;"><a href="/wiki/User_talk:SportingFlyer" title="User talk:SportingFlyer">T</a></span></i>·<i><span style="font-size:small; vertical-align:bottom;"><a href="/wiki/Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer" title="Special:Contributions/SportingFlyer">C</a></span></i> 06:15, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b>. Being a back team member of the coaching staff isn't enough for sport-specific notability and the coverage is inadequate for the GNG. <a href="/wiki/User:No_Great_Shaker" title="User:No Great Shaker">No Great Shaker</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:No_Great_Shaker" title="User talk:No Great Shaker">talk</a>) 10:09, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> per rationale given above. <a href="/wiki/User:Ktrimi991" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Ktrimi991">Ktrimi991</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Ktrimi991" title="User talk:Ktrimi991">talk</a>) 10:34, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> not seeing anything that passes <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:GNG" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:GNG">WP:GNG</a> nor any other notability guideline. Typically assistant coaches do not generate the press to pass notability standards. It's possible he could achieve notability through extensive coverage with his college play (or something else) but I'm not finding any evidence of that. Would change my position if it were discovered and presented.--<a href="/wiki/User:Paulmcdonald" title="User:Paulmcdonald">Paul McDonald</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Paulmcdonald" title="User talk:Paulmcdonald">talk</a>) 12:14, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Comment</b>. Looks like this one's headed to deletion, but I'm finding a fair amount of coverage for a guy who is the associate head coach (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.sfgate.com/collegesports/article/Stanford-names-Anderson-associate-head-coach-12492145.php">here</a>) and defensive coordinator for a Power Five program. Examples of coverage include: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.stanforddaily.com/the-gatekeeper-lance-anderson-and-the-redefinition-of-stanford-football/">this</a> and <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.espn.com/college-football/story/_/id/10346347/lance-anderson-promoted-defensive-coordinator-stanford-cardinal">this</a>. <a href="/wiki/User:Cbl62" title="User:Cbl62">Cbl62</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Cbl62" title="User talk:Cbl62">talk</a>) 01:02, 15 August 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>The ESPN article is interesting, but I'd classify the Stanford article as not independent... hard for me to find more as "Lance Anderson" is a lousy search term. Considering...--<a href="/wiki/User:Paulmcdonald" title="User:Paulmcdonald">Paul McDonald</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Paulmcdonald" title="User talk:Paulmcdonald">talk</a>) 13:39, 15 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></li></ul>

<ul><li><b>Keep</b> I supported keeping this article in the first AfD three years ago. I explained my reasoning in great detail at that time, and feel the same way today. I encourage people to read that debate and the closing statement carefully before coming to a decision. <a href="/wiki/User:Cullen328" title="User:Cullen328"><b style="color:#070">Cullen</b><sup style="color:#707">328</sup></a> <a href="/wiki/User_talk:Cullen328" title="User talk:Cullen328"><span style="color:#00F"><i>Let's discuss it</i></span></a> 08:06, 27 July 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r886049556"/><q class="inline-quote-talk">finding no significant coverage in <i>independent</i>, reliable sources</q>. <span style="border:1px solid;background:#800080"><a href="/wiki/User:Purplebackpack89" title="User:Purplebackpack89"><span style="color:#FFCC00">p</span></a><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Purplebackpack89" title="User talk:Purplebackpack89"><span style="color:#FFCC00;">b</span></a><a href="/wiki/User:Purplebackpack89/C" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Purplebackpack89/C"><span style="color:#FFCC00;">p</span></a></span> 13:47, 27 July 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Keep</b> There are multiple indepdent reliable sources, such as the <i>Salt Lake Tribune</i> article, the section from <i>Hearts Turned to the Fathers</i> and others. Those pushing for deletion are using a far too broad criteria to exclude far too many sources.<a href="/wiki/User:Johnpacklambert" title="User:Johnpacklambert">John Pack Lambert</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Johnpacklambert" title="User talk:Johnpacklambert">talk</a>) 13:50, 27 July 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>
<dl><dd><dl><dd>Very little is actually said about Octaviano Tenorio in the <i>Salt Lake Tribune</i> article, though. It is mostly about ARTURO Tenorio, who found himself in hot water a few years back. The only mention of him is: <link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r886049556"/><q class="inline-quote-talk">His brother, Octaviano Tenorio, was a member of the LDS church's First Quorum of the Seventy</q>. The Salt Lake Tribune article fails the WP:NOTABILITY's mandate for significant coverage. <span style="border:1px solid;background:#800080"><a href="/wiki/User:Purplebackpack89" title="User:Purplebackpack89"><span style="color:#FFCC00">p</span></a><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Purplebackpack89" title="User talk:Purplebackpack89"><span style="color:#FFCC00;">b</span></a><a href="/wiki/User:Purplebackpack89/C" class="mw-redirect" title="User:Purplebackpack89/C"><span style="color:#FFCC00;">p</span></a></span> 13:58, 27 July 2019 (UTC)
<dl><dd>Yes, <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://archive.sltrib.com/article.php?id=54659757&amp;itype=cmsid"><i>The Salt Lake Tribune</i> article</a> only has a one-sentence mention of the subject. This certainly is not <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:SIGCOV" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:SIGCOV">significant coverage</a>, and does not qualify notability. Passing mentions are not significant coverage. This is not an overly broad interpretation of notability guidelines to exclude sources, it is an accurate and correct application of guidelines. <span class="smallcaps" style="font-variant:small-caps;"><a href="/wiki/User:Northamerica1000" title="User:Northamerica1000">North America</a><sup><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Northamerica1000" title="User talk:Northamerica1000"><span style="font-size: x-small;">1000</span></a></sup></span> 21:56, 27 July 2019 (UTC)
<dl><dd>Coverage in the Tribune does in fact add a smidgen of notability; the article mentions him because he held a major position in the Church, and names the position, so it is an independent source on the fact that he held that position. <a href="/wiki/User:E.M.Gregory" title="User:E.M.Gregory">E.M.Gregory</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:E.M.Gregory" title="User talk:E.M.Gregory">talk</a>) 11:50, 29 July 2019 (UTC)
<ul><li>Fact is, though, is that there is no <i>presumed</i> notability for religious subjects on English Wikipedia. The subject may be an important person in the LDS church, but passing mentions do not qualify notability per <i>Wikipedia's standards</i> of notability. <span class="smallcaps" style="font-variant:small-caps;"><a href="/wiki/User:Northamerica1000" title="User:Northamerica1000">North America</a><sup><a href="/wiki/User_talk:Northamerica1000" title="User talk:Northamerica1000"><span style="font-size: x-small;">1000</span></a></sup></span> 18:00, 3 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl></dd></dl>
<p><s>*<b>Note</b> that footnote 6, an article in the academic journal <a href="/wiki/BYU_Studies_Quarterly" title="BYU Studies Quarterly">BYU Studies Quarterly</a>, see the discussion at RS Noticeboard entitled <i>"Are university presses legally affiliated with the Univ. independent of the parent ORG of the University?"</i> This scholarly journal is <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:INDEPENDENT" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:INDEPENDENT">WP:INDEPENDENT</a>.<a href="/wiki/User:E.M.Gregory" title="User:E.M.Gregory">E.M.Gregory</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:E.M.Gregory" title="User talk:E.M.Gregory">talk</a>) </s> 11:50, 29 July 2019 (UTC) <small> Blocked sock <a href="/wiki/User:Rollidan" title="User:Rollidan">Rollidan</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Rollidan" title="User talk:Rollidan">talk</a>) 01:36, 12 August 2019 (UTC) </small>
</p>
<div class="xfd_relist" style="border-top: 1px solid #AAA; border-bottom: 1px solid #AAA; padding: 0px 25px;"><span style="color: #FF6600;"><b><span style="font-size:91%;"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Deletion_process#Relisting_discussions" title="Wikipedia:Deletion process">Relisted</a> to generate a more thorough discussion and clearer consensus.</span></b></span><br />

<div class="xfd_relist" style="border-top: 1px solid #AAA; border-bottom: 1px solid #AAA; padding: 0px 25px;"><span style="color: #FF6600;"><b><span style="font-size:91%;"><a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Deletion_process#Relisting_discussions" title="Wikipedia:Deletion process">Relisted</a> to generate a more thorough discussion and clearer consensus.</span></b></span><br />
<small>Please add new comments below this notice. Thanks, <a href="/wiki/User:Rollidan" title="User:Rollidan">Rollidan</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Rollidan" title="User talk:Rollidan">talk</a>) 01:37, 12 August 2019 (UTC)</small></div>

<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Marcello_Catalano"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Marcello_Catalano&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Marcello Catalano (page does not exist)">Marcello Catalano</a></span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Marcello_Catalano&amp;action=edit&amp;section=T-1" title="Edit section: ">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h3>
<dl><dd><span id="Marcello_Catalano"></span><span class="plainlinks nourlexpansion lx"><a href="/w/index.php?title=Marcello_Catalano&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Marcello Catalano (page does not exist)">Marcello Catalano</a> (<a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Marcello_Catalano&amp;action=edit">edit</a>&#160;&#124; <a href="/w/index.php?title=Talk:Marcello_Catalano&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Talk:Marcello Catalano (page does not exist)">talk</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Marcello_Catalano&amp;action=history">history</a><span class="sysop-show">&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Marcello_Catalano&amp;action=protect">protect</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Marcello_Catalano&amp;action=delete">delete</a></span>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Whatlinkshere/Marcello_Catalano&amp;limit=999">links</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Marcello_Catalano&amp;action=watch">watch</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Special:Log&amp;page=Marcello+Catalano">logs</a>&#160;&#124; <a class="external text" href="//tools.wmflabs.org/pageviews?pages=Marcello_Catalano&amp;project=en.wikipedia.org">views</a>)</span> – (<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Marcello_Catalano" title="Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Marcello Catalano">View AfD</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <span class="plainlinks"><a class="external text" href="https://tools.wmflabs.org/jackbot/snottywong/cgi-bin/votecounter.cgi?page=Wikipedia:Articles_for_deletion/Marcello_Catalano">Stats</a></span>)</dd>
<dd>(<span class="plainlinks"><i>Find sources:</i>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?as_eq=wikipedia&amp;q=%22Marcello+Catalano%22">Google</a> (<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?tbs=bks:1&amp;q=%22Marcello+Catalano%22+-wikipedia">books</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?tbm=nws&amp;q=%22Marcello+Catalano%22+-wikipedia">news</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.google.com/search?&amp;q=%22Marcello+Catalano%22+site:news.google.com/newspapers&amp;source=newspapers">newspapers</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//scholar.google.com/scholar?q=%22Marcello+Catalano%22">scholar</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/search?safe=off&amp;tbs=sur:fmc&amp;tbm=isch&amp;q=%22Marcello+Catalano%22+-site:wikipedia.org+-site:wikimedia.org">free images</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.google.com/custom?hl=en&amp;cx=007734830908295939403%3Agalkqgoksq0&amp;cof=FORID%3A13%3BAH%3Aleft%3BCX%3AWikipedia%2520Reference%2520Search&amp;q=%22Marcello+Catalano%22">WP refs</a>)&#160;<b>·</b> <a class="external text" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Free_English_newspaper_sources">FENS</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.jstor.org/action/doBasicSearch?Query=%22Marcello+Catalano%22&amp;acc=on&amp;wc=on">JSTOR</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.nytimes.com/search/%22Marcello+Catalano%22">NYT</a>&#160;<b>·</b> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://wikipedialibrary.wmflabs.org/partners/">TWL</a></span>)</dd></dl>
<p>Fails <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:PROF" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:PROF">WP:PROF</a>/<a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:ACADEMIC" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:ACADEMIC">WP:ACADEMIC</a>. The subject has no peer reviewed papers according to <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://scholar.google.com/scholar?as_q=&amp;as_sauthors=%22Marcello+Catalano%22">GScholar</a>, only one paper not published in a plant society magazine (a society called AIPC which he set up), and a self published book. The subject also has no academic ranking in any standard index such as Researchgate. The primary author of the article <a href="/wiki/User:Rafflesiana" title="User:Rafflesiana">User:Rafflesiana</a> also appears to be the subject of the page which suggests a possible <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:COI" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:COI">COI</a>. Propose to delete. <a href="/w/index.php?title=User:Nyababair&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="User:Nyababair (page does not exist)">Nyababair</a> (<a href="/w/index.php?title=User_talk:Nyababair&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="User talk:Nyababair (page does not exist)">talk</a>) 00:19, 12 August 2019 (UTC)
</p>
<ul><li><b>Delete</b> a non-notable academic.<a href="/wiki/User:Johnpacklambert" title="User:Johnpacklambert">John Pack Lambert</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Johnpacklambert" title="User talk:Johnpacklambert">talk</a>) 16:16, 17 August 2019 (UTC)</li>
<li><b>Delete</b> Fails <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:PROF" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikipedia:PROF">WP:PROF</a> <a href="/wiki/User:Taewangkorea" title="User:Taewangkorea">Taewangkorea</a> (<a href="/wiki/User_talk:Taewangkorea" title="User talk:Taewangkorea">talk</a>) 04:11, 18 August 2019 (UTC)</li></ul>

<dl><dd><i>The above discussion is preserved as an archive of the debate. <b style="color:red">Please do not modify it.</b> Subsequent comments should be made on the appropriate discussion page (such as the article's <a href="/wiki/Help:Using_talk_pages" class="mw-redirect" title="Help:Using talk pages">talk page</a> or in a <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:Deletion_review" title="Wikipedia:Deletion review">deletion review</a>). No further edits should be made to this page.</i></dd></dl></div>
